# Task 7 – SLA Creation

## Project

**Virtual Agent–Driven SLA Breach Awareness & Justification System**

---

## Objective

This task configures a Service Level Agreement (SLA) for Incident Resolution using ServiceNow Administration. The SLA monitors incident resolution time based on business hours and supports proactive SLA governance.

---

## Navigation

**Service Level Management → SLA Definitions**

---

## SLA Configuration

| Field | Value |
|------|------|
| Name | Incident Resolution - Virtual Agent Governance |
| Type | SLA |
| Target | Resolution |
| Table | Incident |
| Active | True |
| Duration Type | User Specified |
| Duration | 8 Hours |
| Schedule Source | SLA Definition |
| Schedule | IT Support Business Hours |

---

## Steps Performed

- Opened SLA Definitions
- Created a new SLA
- Configured Incident Resolution target
- Set Duration to 8 Hours
- Associated Business Schedule
- Activated the SLA
- Saved the configuration

---

## Deliverables

- SLA Definition
- Incident Resolution Configuration
- Business Schedule Association
- Configuration Screenshots

---

## Expected Result

A new SLA named **Incident Resolution - Virtual Agent Governance** is successfully created and configured to monitor Incident resolution time during IT Support business hours.

---

## Status

**Completed**

